Hello

I am using psycopg2 2.7.7 to connect to the EDB Postgres Advanced Server using asynchronous support (async=1). When I ran the following procedure:
CREATE OR REPLACE PROCEDURE compile_test
AS
    v_day DATE;
    v_next_day DATE;
BEGIN
    SELECT NOW ITO v_day;
   SELECT NOW()+1 Day INTO v_next_day;
   DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE(v_day);
   DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE(v_next_day);
END;

**on PSQL Prompt**: It is throwing all the errors when run on psql prompt. Refer the screenshot

<img width="940" alt="psql_prompt" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1632882/53715617-5edc3c00-3e78-11e9-8940-d1ceb51fbacc.png">

**on Python Prompt using psycpog2**: It returns only one error "ERROR: compilation of SPL function/procedure "compile_test" failed due to 2 errors SQL state: 42601". Which is the last error of the psql prompt. Refer the screenshot:

![psycopg2_multiple_error](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1632882/53715758-d0b48580-3e78-11e9-8978-8de9edb0f05f.png)


How can we read all the errors when psycopg2.ProgrammingError exception occurs ? Can anyone please provide some pointers, suggestions or it is a bug in psycopg2?

