When I launch the application with a ssh tunnel outside of the thread it starts up perfectly fine, yet when I move the tunnel into the thread none of my routes load and I end up getting timeout errors.

This is launched using the tiangolo/uwsgi-nginx-flask:python3.6 docker container. I have multi-threading enabled within my uwsgi.ini file as well. 

When launching the docker container with the ssh connection in the thread I get the following output:
```flask_uwsgi_testing | 2018-02-23 03:41:08,567| ERROR   | Problem setting SSH Forwarder up: Couldn't open tunnel localhost:4507 <> my_server.com:3306 might be in use or destination not reachable```


